data.title: Utah Jazz Roster
data.meta_description: Utah Jazz scores, news, schedule, players, stats, rumors, depth charts and more on RealGM.com
data.text:
Morris Almond was selected as the #25 pick in the First Round of the 2007 NBA Draft by the Utah Jazz. Morris Almond signed a multi-year contract with the Utah Jazz on July 6, 2007.

Ronnie Brewer was selected as the #14 pick in the First Round of the 2006 NBA Draft by the Utah Jazz. Ronnie Brewer signed a multi-year contract with the Utah Jazz on July 7, 2006.

Jarron Collins was selected as the #24 pick in the Second Round of the 2001 NBA Draft by the Utah Jazz. Jarron Collins signed a contract with the Utah Jazz on September 24, 2001. Jarron Collins re-signed to a multi-year contract as a free agent with the Utah Jazz on July 24, 2002. Jarron Collins re-signed to a multi-year contract as a free agent with the Utah Jazz on July 23, 2004. Jarron Collins re-signed to a multi-year contract as a free agent with the Utah Jazz on July 20, 2006.

Andrei Kirilenko was selected as the #24 pick in the First Round of the 1999 NBA Draft by the Utah Jazz. Andrei Kirilenko signed a multi-year contract with the Utah Jazz on August 16, 2001. Andrei Kirilenko signed a multi-year extension with the Utah Jazz on October 29, 2004.

C.J. Miles was selected as the #4 pick in the Second Round of the 2005 NBA Draft by the Utah Jazz. C.J. Miles signed a multi-year contract with the Utah Jazz on July 11, 2005. C.J. Miles re-signed to a contract as a free agent with the Utah Jazz on October 1, 2007.

Paul Millsap was selected as the #17 pick in the Second Round of the 2006 NBA Draft by the Utah Jazz. Paul Millsap signed a multi-year contract with the Utah Jazz on August 1, 2006.
